
Ranger Help for: setprime
=========================

SYNTAX:      setprime/setprime <your primary terrain name here>
USAGE:       Any wilderness terrain.

SUMMARY:    
Allows the Ranger to set his or her first primary terrain. Available
terrains are: 

         forest  plains  swamp  desert  jungle  hills
         beach   arctic  barren underground  mountain 

A Ranger's primary terrain is the terrain in which he/she grew up in. A
Ranger's primary terrain will affect such things as fighting, allowing
him/her to fight better due the fact that he/she knows the terrain better.
It will also affect what kinds of followers a Ranger might attract, or
what kinds of animals he/she might try to sooth. It will affect almost
everything a Ranger does, choose it carefully.

Choose your primary terrain carefully. Changing it later requires Warden
Thorn's reattunement ritual. Use 'rhelp reattune' for details.

NOTE: Primary and secondary terrains can be the same.

